blog.title: Target X
blog.description:
X-23 is the product of a top-secret project that attempted to recreate the original Weapon X. Cloned from a damaged DNA sample of Wolverine, X-23 was programmed to be the perfect killing machine.

She goes by Laura Kinney, a name given to her by her genetic creator/surrogate mother, Sarah Kinney.

Her official X-Men codename - before Wolverine - was Talon.

X-23 was created by Craig Kyle and Chris Yost, and first appeared on X-Men: Evolution.

If we post your art and you want it credited differently/taken down, please message us.

summary: Disney to Kick Marvel Movies off Netflix
title: Disney to Kick Marvel Movies off Netflix
excerpt: The war of the streaming services heats up as the Disney streaming service targets big titles on Netflix
description:
The war of the streaming services continues…

More details have trickled through about Disney’s upcoming streaming service, and Netflix isn’t going to be happy about it. As expected, the new platform will exclusively house all their new Marvel movies, starting with Captain Marvel, alongside other big titles like Dumbo, Lady And The Tramp, and Noelle.

Interestingly, anything that’s already licensed to Netflix – including older Marvel and Star Wars movies up to and including Ant Man And The Wasp and Solo – will remain on the rival site, with Disney apparently having no plans to steal them back anytime soon. This deal also includes Marvel shows like Jessica Jones and Luke Cage…
